TerminalPrinter - Class in print
This class is a Terminal implementation of the Printer interface, hence all output is sent to standard output.
TerminalPrinter() - Constructor for class print.TerminalPrinter
Constructor (using defaults): creates a Printer with zero level of debug, timestamping active using format according to ISO 8601.
TerminalPrinter(TerminalPrinter.Builder) - Constructor for class print.TerminalPrinter
Constructor using builder.
TerminalPrinter.Builder - Class in print
Builder pattern: allows the caller to specify the attributes that it wants to change and keep the default values in the others.
TerminalPrinter.Builder(int, boolean) - Constructor for class print.TerminalPrinter.Builder
The Printer created uses, by default, timestamping format according to ISO 8601.
